 part of goldman sachs international before embarking on his own with the founding of caxton in  caxton closed its fund to new investors the fund then opened and closed intermittently and most recently reopened to new investors in august  it was reported that at the end of the s caxton global investments volatility fell substantially along with the funds returns in  concern at caxton associates around the potential future impact on their historical rate of return due to their funds size resulted in  percent of investors capital being returned assets under management post  were  billion on december   caxtoniseman capital a joint investment partnership caxton associates and frederick iseman announced that it had completed its spinoff from caxton associates caxtoniseman capital will change its name to ci capital partners llc in  bruce kovner stepped back from trading and appointed andrew law as caxton’s chief investment officer in  law was appointed as the chairman ceo and controlling general partner of caxton associates following the retirement of kovner law joined the london office in  from goldman sachs where he was managing director and head of ficc proprietary trading in london  financial crisisedit during the  financial crisis caxton associates did not erect gates freezing investor capital in their caxton global investments fund as reported the fund saw client redemptions totalling  of assets under management through –—while returning  for the year the redemptions were reportedly born out of cash strapped clients many of whose asset allocations were gated and frozen at other investment management companies two years later the firm had fallen from no  to no  in  it was reported that since  caxton associates had returned  billion to clients whilst managing  billion ranking second amongst managers who have returned more than they currently manage companyedit caxton associates offices are in new york londons mayfair district sydney and princeton nj investmentsedit ca